FOR INTERACTIVE MAP & CASE STUDY 
https://api.worldanimalprotection.org/methodology

The Animal Protection Index  (API) is assessed according to 10 indicators and grouped in 4 goals 
- 4 goals: 
	1) recognition of animal sentience and prohibition of animal suffereing 
	2) PRESENCE OF ANIMAL WELFARE LEGISLATION -> which we will be focusing on
	   https://api.worldanimalprotection.org/indicators#Legislation
		a) laws that apply to animals in captivity 
		b) laws that apply for animals used for draught and recreation 
		c) laws that apply the animals used in scientific research 
		d) laws that apply to wild animals -> which we will be focusing on 
			https://api.worldanimalprotection.org/indicators#Legislation
			- countries are ranked from A (ligh bright green) to G (dark red)
			- A countries  score ‘A’ for this indicator because its legislation contains:
				- Ban on sport and recreational hunting.
				- Wildlife management uses hunting only as a last resort, after demonstrating that all other alternatives have failed.
				- The cruellest forms of hunting are banned (i.e. dog hunting, live baiting, poisoning, trapping, falconry, bow hunting).
		worse country is Ukraine, and best is Kenya 
	3) establishment of supportive governmemt bodies 
	4) support for international animal wefare satandards 



